<HR>
<A NAME="coa">
<h2>National emblem</h2></a>


<P><A HREF="../images/k/kw).gif">
<IMG SRC="../images/k/kw).gif" ALT="[Coat of arms of Kuwait]" WIDTH=213 HEIGHT=220 BORDER=0 ALIGN=bottom></A><br>
from the website of the Kuwaiti embassy in Argentina</P>

<blockquote>"The emblem of Kuwait consisted of 'a helmet with a falcon and two
intersecting flags over it' until the middle of 1963, when the
Council of Ministers decided to replace it with a new one. The
present emblem of Kuwait is a falcon with outspread wings embracing a
<I>dhow</I> (boom) sailing on blue and white waves. It is a symbol of
Kuwait's maritime tradition."</blockquote>
<p><b>Source:</b> the <I>Kuwait Information Center</I> (website defunct)<br>
The inscription is "<I>Dawlat ul-Kuwait</I>" (State of Kuwait).<br>
<I>Dov Gutterman</I>, 21 Mar 2001</p>

